main event: One round white & green object was observed descending toward the Earth before leveling off and climbing slightly, as seen on 5 December 1956.
interesting points: The observed object was described as initially white but turned green as it descended., The sighting lasted for approximately 20 to 30 seconds., The object was noted to change altitude and speed, causing astonishment among observers., Weather conditions were clear at the time of the observation., The report suggests that the sighting was likely a meteor, attributed to optical illusion.
witness description: Military personnel involved in the observation
